Context
The client wants the existing React/TypeScript StyloBliss SaaS landing page converted to plain HTML, CSS, and JavaScript files — pixel-perfect, same colors, same navigation, same UI, same interactions. The target output directory is vanila-website/ at the project root. No build tools, no frameworks, no dependencies. Must open directly in any browser.

CRITICAL CONSTRAINT — Zero UI Changes
Every new file must be a 1:1 exact replica of what the React app renders. No changes to:

Colors, gradients, shadows, or opacity values
Font sizes, weights, letter-spacing, or line-height
Spacing, padding, margin, or max-width values
Layout or component structure
Text content, headings, labels, or copy
Images, icons, or SVG paths
Animations, transitions, timing, or interaction behaviors
Navigation items, link labels, or page routes

The only permitted changes are the technology translation itself (JSX → HTML, Tailwind classes → equivalent CSS, Framer Motion → CSS/JS animations, React Router <Link> → <a href>). If a value exists in the React source, copy it verbatim.


